      "order": 1,
      "Description": "Healthcare organisations are increasingly turning to AI tools to streamline operations, yet this shift brings significant regulatory and legal risks that many teams are unprepared for. This lesson explores how the use of AI in clinical and administrative settings can create new compliance challenges under frameworks such as HIPAA in the United States and GDPR across the United Kingdom and Europe. You will learn why AI systems that process patient data may inadvertently breach data protection rules, generate liability, or fall foul of consent requirements. We will also look at practical examples of where things can go wrong, helping you to recognise the warning signs before they become costly problems. By the end of this lesson, you will have a clearer understanding of why adopting AI responsibly requires a solid grasp of the compliance landscape.",
